the silences of the palace ( tunisian arabic : صمت القصور , samt el qusur ) is a 1994 tunisian film co-written and directed by moufida tlatli .   the film investigates issues of gender , class and sexuality in the arab world through the lives of two generations of women at a prince 's palace .   seen through the eyes of an attractive young wedding singer , it exposes the sexual and social servitude of a group of women in an elaborate palace during the french protectorate in tunisia .   tlatli wrote the film in response to her own mother 's sudden severe illness and her subsequent realization of how little she knew about her life .